igure --disable-shared --enable-static --with-openssl --with-tpm2` - configures build\n3. `make -j16` - builds library successfully  \n4. `make -C tests fuzz` - fails on fuzzer compilation\n\n**Critical Issue**: The fuzzer Makefile likely doesn\'t inherit the correct include paths from the main build. The `tests/Makefile` may need additional `AM_CPPFLAGS` or `AM_CXXFLAGS` to include the build directory.\n\n**Additional Warning**: There\'s also a warning about `EVP_CIPHER_CTX_get_iv_length` being undeclared in `CryptSym.c:466`. This suggests OpenSSL version compatibility issues, but this is not the primary build failure.\n\n**Recommended Investigation Steps:**\n1. Examine the `tests/Makefile` to see how fuzzer compilation flags are set\n2. Check the `fuzz.cc` source file to understand include paths\n3. Look at the build script (`build.sh`) to see if include paths are properly set\n4. Check if headers are installed to `/usr/local/include` or similar system paths\n5. Consider modifying the build process to install headers before fuzzer compilation\n\n--- 【LESSONS FROM PREVIOUS ATTEMPTS】 ---\n- [Attempt 1] First build attempt shows successful library compilation but fuzzer compilation fails due to missing header \'libtpms/tpm_library.h\'. The issue appears to be include path configuration - fuzzer expects headers in libtpms/ subdirectory but they may be installed elsewhere or need different compiler flags. Need to examine the build configuration and header installation locations.\n- [Attempt 2] Fix partially successful - resolved tpm_library.h not found error but revealed chain dependency issue. The generated tpm_library.h includes tpm_types.h which is also missing. Need to examine header inclusion paths more comprehensively. The build directory include path was added but may need additional paths for nested includes.\n- [Attempt 1] The library compilation succeeded but fuzzer build failed due to missing header file. The fuzz.cc file expects libtpms/tpm_library.h but it