ry.h includes tpm_types.h which is also missing. Need to examine header inclusion paths more comprehensively. The build directory include path was added but may need additional paths for nested includes.\n- [Attempt 1] The library compilation succeeded but fuzzer build failed due to missing header file. The fuzz.cc file expects libtpms/tpm_library.h but it\'s not found in the include path. This suggests either: 1) Header not installed to expected location, 2) Include paths not set correctly for fuzzer build, or 3) Header file has different name/location in source tree.\n- [Attempt 2] Fix partially successful - resolved tpm_library.h not found error but revealed chain dependency issue. The generated tpm_library.h includes tpm_types.h which is also missing. Need to examine header inclusion paths more comprehensively. The build directory include path was added but may need additional paths for nested includes. The tpm_types.h file exists in source tree but not in build directory, and the relative include path in tpm_library.h doesn\'t work with current include paths.\n\n\n--- Configuration Files (Dockerfile, build.sh, etc.) ---\n\n### Content from: Dockerfile ###\n# Copyright 2019 Google Inc.\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\n#\n################################################################################\n\nFROM gcr.io/oss-fuzz-base/base-builder@sha256:24ece23c6e7e4483fd49b19c31e4084992088b58a902c3c45d74d10541f3aa40\nRUN \\\n        apt-get update && \\\n        apt-get install -y \\\n        make autoconf automake libtool \\\n        libstdc++-9-dev \\\n        libssl-dev libseccomp-dev pkg-config\nRUN git clone  https://github.com/stefanberger/libtpms libtpms\nWORKDIR libtpms\nCOPY build.sh $SRC/\n\n### Content from: build.sh ###\n#!/bin/bash -eu\n# Copyright 2019 Google Inc.\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\n#\n################################################################################\n\n#!/bin/bash -eu\n# Copyright 2019 Google Inc.\n#\n# Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the "License");\n# you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n# You may obtain a copy of the License at\n#\n#      http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n#\n# Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n# distributed under the License is distributed on an "AS IS" BASIS,\n# WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n# See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n# limitations under the License.\n#\n################################################################################\n\n# Set include paths for the fuzzer build\nexport CFLAGS="$CFLAGS -I/work/build/include"\nexport CXXFLAGS="$CXXFLAGS -I/work/build/include"\n\ntests/oss-fuzz.sh\n\n### Content from: project.yaml ###\nhomepage: "https://github.com/stefanberger/libtpms"\nlanguage: c++\nprimary_contact: "stefanb@us.ibm.com"\nauto_ccs:\n  - "ml